            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>ΑΧ̣[- -] could be restored as dedication to Achilles (in the Dative or Genitive), or alternatively as a theophoric name, e.g. Achillodoros, 
                    which could be in the Nom. and followed by a deity's name in the Dative. The placement on the lip of 
                a cup is typical for dedications, but also to sympotic inscriptions. Less likely it is an ownership inscription - these more often appear on underside of 
                cups.</p>
            </div>
